Description: Behavior for disabling the power stage duringmovement.0 / Disable Immediately /diSi: Disablepower stage immediately1 / Disable After Halt /diSh: Disable powerstage after deceleration to standstillThis parameter specifies the response to a powerstage disable request.Halt is used for deceleration to standstill.Modified settings become active immediately.Available with firmware version ≥V01.26.
Parameter address via fieldbus: CANopen 605B:0hModbus 1684Profibus 1684CIP 106.1.74ModbusTCP 1684EtherCAT 605B:0hPROFINET 1684
